Technology Stack:

Frontend/Web Version: HTML5, CSS3 (with 3D transformations), JavaScript.

Desktop Version: Python with Tkinter, Canvas, and 3D-style widgets.

Use Cases:

A modern alternative to standard calculator apps.

Great for educational purposes to demonstrate UI/UX concepts.

Can be extended into a scientific or programmable calculator.

Innovation:
The standout feature of this calculator lies in its 3D visual presentation, making it not only functional but also visually stimulating. It mimics physical button press depth and uses lighting effects to create a realistic 3D look.

